<subSubSection id="C339652BFF9EF815FF13FECDDD479564" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9C36A0FF9EF815FF13FECDDD479564" blockId="27.[151,1437,367,573]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FF13FECDDEEA96D0" author="Maquart, P. O. &amp; Malec, P." box="[151,434,367,393]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="441 - 444" refId="ref17466" refString="Maquart, P. O. &amp; Malec, P. (2017) On the distribution and natural history of a rarely encountered species: Goliathus (Fornasinius) klingbeili Zoller, Fiebig, &amp; Schulz, 1995 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Cetoniinae). Zootaxa, 4341 (3), 441 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4341.3.12" type="journal article" year="2017">Maquart &amp; Malec (2017)</bibRefCitation>
mention 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FD98FECDDCD496D0" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[540,908,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Goliathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="higginsi" subGenus="Fornasinius">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FD98FECDDDD296D0" box="[540,650,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Goliathus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FD1FFECDDC7A96D1" box="[667,802,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fornasinius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FCB6FECDDCD496D0" box="[818,908,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">higginsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as being reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F3347630FF9EF815FB25FECDDBB296D0" box="[1185,1258,367,393]" name="Ghana" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ghana</collectingCountry>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FA8AFECDDFBC96F4" author="Mudge, A. D. &amp; Orozco, J. &amp; Philips, T. K. &amp; Antoine, P." pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="113 - 174" refId="ref17706" refString="Mudge, A. D., Orozco, J., Philips, T. K. &amp; Antoine, P. (2012) The cetoniine fauna of the Upper Guinean forests and savannas of Ghana (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Cetoniinae). Terrestrial Arthropod Reviews, 5, 113 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187498312 X 635319" type="journal article" year="2012">
Mudge 
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FAE0FECDDAC596D0" box="[1380,1437,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, but this citation is incorrect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FDA9FE31DC4D96F4" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[557,789,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Fornasinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="higginsi">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FDA9FE31DC4D96F4" box="[557,789,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fornasinius higginsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, is recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F3347630FF9EF815FBCAFE31DBCF96F4" box="[1102,1175,403,429]" name="Ghana" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ghana</collectingCountry>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FB3EFE31DAC496F4" author="Beinhundner, G." box="[1210,1436,403,429]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref16250" refString="Beinhundner, G. (2017) The Cetoniinae of Africa. Privately published, Euerbach, 1174 + XXIV pp." type="book" year="2017">Beinhundner (2017)</bibRefCitation>
and is known from the Eastern and Western regions (D. Moore, M. De Palma, personal communication). The other 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FF13FE79DE4696AD" authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1852" box="[151,286,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Fornasinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FF13FE79DE4696AD" box="[151,286,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fornasinius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known from 
<collectingCountry id="F3347630FF9EF815FD92FE79DD3A96AC" box="[534,610,475,501]" name="Ghana" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ghana</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FDEBFE79DB3B96AC" authority="Zoller, Fiebig &amp; Schulze, 1995" authorityName="Zoller, Fiebig, &amp; Schulze" authorityYear="1995" box="[623,1123,474,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Fornasinius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klingbeili">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FDEBFE79DDAF96AC" box="[623,759,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">F. klingbeili</emphasis>
Zöller, Fiebig &amp; Schulze, 1995
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Eastern and 
<collectingRegion id="49E7F842FF9EF815FF42FE5DDE599540" box="[198,257,511,537]" country="Ghana" name="Volta" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Volta</collectingRegion>
Regions as well as neighboring 
<collectingCountry id="F3347630FF9EF815FDEAFE5DDDF29540" box="[622,682,511,537]" name="Togo" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Togo</collectingCountry>
, where the larvae were collected in hyrax (Afrotheria: Hyracoidea) middens (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FE80FD81DD4B9564" author="Maquart, P. O. &amp; Malec, P." box="[260,531,547,573]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="441 - 444" refId="ref17466" refString="Maquart, P. O. &amp; Malec, P. (2017) On the distribution and natural history of a rarely encountered species: Goliathus (Fornasinius) klingbeili Zoller, Fiebig, &amp; Schulz, 1995 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Cetoniinae). Zootaxa, 4341 (3), 441 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4341.3.12" type="journal article" year="2017">Maquart &amp; Malec 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
